{
  "stem": "13313.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as we left the park and crossed the boulevard along the park, which I believe is called the Quinten [?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Matsijslei, ?] Quinten Matsijs, I think, was a famous artist, or painter.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "All of the streets in the area were named after the Flemish painters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We stopped dead in our tracks because right in front of us, we saw a horrible scene.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The-- we saw German officers, in beautiful shiny uniforms and big shiny boots, on the street, pick up, grab whoever had the star-- that's what the purpose of wearing the star, star of-- and just pick the people off the street and pushed them in those trucks.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And just as we stood there ready to cross into that area, the picture that will always be my mind was of a little old lady, little old woman, tiny, with a shawl over her head.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't remember what day of the week it was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and she was kind of, her hands folded, on her knees begging to be let go because her family was waiting.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I remember that they just-- she was very small, and he was very big and just grabbed her, and literally threw her into the truck with the other people.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when my mother saw that, she immediately made an about-turn.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we went back to out home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that's where we knew, that's when we saw the naked truth of what this was all about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That was the day of revelation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And-- so Mother realized that it was very dangerous to circulate, and especially with children because wherever there were-- we noticed, we had noticed or heard that, if you're-- if you're caught [INAUDIBLE] with their children, there would be no-- no two ways about it, we'll just be deported.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
